{% block metaDescription %}
    "Family: Colubridae, subfamily Calamarinae. Max. length: 40 cm. Occurrence in Taiwan: 	
    Throughout Taiwan and Orchid Island, up to 1500 m altitude. Rare. Global Distribution: 
    India (Assam), W. Malaysia (incl. Pulau Tioman), Thailand, Laos, Vietnam, Cambodia, Myanmar, 
    South China (Hainan, Fujian, Guangdong, Guangxi, Guizhou, Sichuan, Yunnan, Zhejiang), Taiwan, 
    Japan (Ryukyu Islands). Description: Small snake; total length up to 40 cm. There are 13 rows of 
    scales, all are smooth and iridescent. Head is small and not distinct from neck, but the shields 
    are large; the prefrontals are enlarged (slightly longer than broad) and there are no loreals, 
    temporals or internasals. Body is cylindrical and slender; tail is short, ending in a spine. Eye 
    is small, bead-like;"
